Abati, Iran'''Abati''' is a surname. It was used by an ancient noble family of Florence.Notable people with the surname include:*Antonio Abati (died 1667), Italian poet*Baldo Angelo Abati (sixteenth century), Italian naturalist*Joaquín Abati (1865-1936), Spanish writer*Joël Abati (born 1970), French handball player*Megliore degli Abati (thirteenth century), Italian poet*Niccolò dell'Abbate (1509 or 1512-1571), Italian painter*Reuben Abati (born 1965), Nigerian newspaper columnistOther uses* Abati, Iran, village in Iran* Marauna abati, species of beetle in the family CerambycidaeReferencesAbati